SIMPLE: dionysian
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dionysian
<hw>Di`o*ny"sian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Relating to
Dionysius, a monk of the 6th century; <as>as, the <ex>Dionysian</ex>, or
Christian, era</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dionysian period</b></col>, <cd>a period of 532 years,
depending on the cycle of the sun, or 28 years, and the cycle of the
moon, or 19 years; -- sometimes called the <altname>Greek paschal
cycle</altname>, or <altname>Victorian period</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diophantine</ent>⟦br⟧
